function minimumXorSum(nums1, nums2) {
    nums2.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let xorSum = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < nums1.length; i++) {
        xorSum += nums1[i] ^ nums2[i];
    }
    return xorSum;
}
```

    The algorithm to minimize XOR sum works as follows:

1. Sort the array nums2 in ascending order.
2. Calculate the XOR sum between elements of array nums1 and nums2, iterating through both arrays simultaneously.
3. Return the XOR sum of the two arrays.

By sorting the nums2 array, we are effectively minimizing the XOR sum because when doing bitwise XOR, if the corresponding bit is 1 in one number and 0 in the other number, the resultant bit will be 1. Sorting nums2 guarantees that we minimize the number of 1's in the resultant XOR operation.

